content.text:
I don't know why I'm like this, but string cheese has always sort of bothered me existentially. I've always imagined it as a sort of dairy-plastic hybrid, sort of the way I used to think of tofu... hey wait a minute, could I be wrong? I was wrong about tofu, so maybe string cheese is Good Actually after all?

No way, introspection is *way* harder than clinging to your pre-existing beliefs.
